1
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:19,000
Anonyma

2
00:00:26,458 --> 00:00:30,500
A Woman in Berlin

3
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:38,500
Who would've thought that?

4
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:43,292
On April 16th 1945 the time had come.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,875
The Russian army had surrounded Berlin

6
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,792
and now they were heading
towards the Reichstag.

7
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:57,250
On this day,
you could see the sun behind the clouds,

8
00:00:57,417 --> 00:01:01,500
and the smell of lilac
wafted through all the smoke.

9
00:01:05,792 --> 00:01:08,458
How to start?

10
00:01:08,583 --> 00:01:11,625
How to find the right words?

11
00:01:13,917 --> 00:01:17,042
I've been a journalist,
I've traveled 12 countries.

12
00:01:17,208 --> 00:01:19,500
Been living in Moscow,
Paris and London.

13
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:21,958
I really liked to stay
in Paris and London.

14
00:01:23,542 --> 00:01:28,458
I decided to come back.
I wanted to be part of it.

15
00:01:32,875 --> 00:01:35,833
My name doesn't matter.

16
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,125
I am one of the many who fervently
believed in our country's future.

17
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:44,000
Doubts?
Only weak persons had doubts.

18
00:01:44,167 --> 00:01:46,583
Warsaw, Brussels, Paris.
We're always winning.

19
00:01:46,583 --> 00:01:49,167
The Russians don't have a leader.

20
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,250
When they finally come to their senses,

21
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:53,958
we are already knocking at
their front door in Moscow.

22
00:01:56,292 --> 00:02:00,333
Pardon our pushiness,
but it's war after all.

23
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:02,042
Gerd hated railway stations.

24
00:02:02,042 --> 00:02:05,042
When he left, the sound of
his boots filled the house.

25
00:02:06,958 --> 00:02:09,542
We were certain to do the right thing,

26
00:02:09,542 --> 00:02:11,708
we breathed the same
air as everybody else.

27
00:02:11,708 --> 00:02:12,500
We were part of this.

28
00:02:13,917 --> 00:02:15,708
And then he takes off my coat and says:

29
00:02:15,708 --> 00:02:18,583
The Russians have no idea
what's coming towards them.

30
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:24,250
So we were heading towards the
Sorbonne and chatting away in French.

31
00:02:24,417 --> 00:02:28,417
He thought that I was one
of those tall blond Swedes.

32
00:02:28,583 --> 00:02:32,583
Then I made a double step
to match my stride to his.

33
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:36,833
That's when he stopped and said:
"Ah, a daughter of the Fuhrer"

34
00:02:37,708 --> 00:02:41,375
That was the end of the acquaintance.
What a pity.

35
00:02:42,417 --> 00:02:46,500
Hold on. I... I'd like to...
Stop the music, please.

36
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:54,042
I would like for us all
to share this moment,

37
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:57,875
this wonderful evening,
with our husbands

38
00:02:58,083 --> 00:03:02,083
who are stationed
somewhere all over Europe.

39
00:03:20,042 --> 00:03:21,917
Get lost!

40
00:03:22,083 --> 00:03:23,875
Run, run!

41
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:25,417
Get away!

42
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:31,375
Go away!
Houses on the right. Fan out.

43
00:03:42,792 --> 00:03:44,792
Come here, damn it!

44
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:47,875
Mummy, where are you?

45
00:03:48,417 --> 00:03:51,333
Come on. Hurry.

46
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:18,750
Away. Go away.

47
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:23,917
Open fire, reload grenade.

48
00:04:24,958 --> 00:04:26,958
...and fire!

49
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:34,917
Fire!

50
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:37,417
Shit.

51
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:43,875
- Wait for me.
- Watch out! Heads down.

52
00:04:45,042 --> 00:04:47,958
- There you are.
- Stop! Wait for me.

53
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:49,125
Watch out!

54
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:53,542
No!

55
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:04,292
No uniforms, no weapons,
or it's martial law.

56
00:05:09,792 --> 00:05:12,708
Felix, where are you?

57
00:05:15,417 --> 00:05:16,833
Felix?

58
00:05:17,417 --> 00:05:22,125
- Where the hell is he? Felix?
- Not a single order.

59
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:26,458
No messages, nothing at all.
Nobody gives a shit about us.

60
00:05:26,958 --> 00:05:31,042
Felix? Lenchen, Lenchen?
Where are you, damn it?

61
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:35,500
In Wedding district, they are already
showing their toddlers to the Russians.

62
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:36,875
Russian pigs.

63
00:05:37,042 --> 00:05:41,333
That were the book dealers.
They sometimes speak French.

64
00:05:43,917 --> 00:05:46,917
And that's the pharmacist's widow.

65
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:52,042
Her husband once cured Minister
Hindenburg's headache.

66
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:53,083
That's over.

67
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:57,042
Now you step on the face
and the arms of a dead woman

68
00:05:57,542 --> 00:06:00,583
only to get a glass of jelly.

69
00:06:03,542 --> 00:06:08,750
That's the quiet Mrs. Binder.
Musician. Her husband is MIA.

70
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:17,708
Can someone help?
She is suffocating.

71
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Look at me. Look at me!

72
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:27,417
I will write all of this down,
I will report it.

73
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:31,625
Gerd, and you shall read it.

74
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:34,917
May I offer you something?

75
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,083
Thank you.

76
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,042
From Silesia.
She won't make it.

77
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:37,792
Go, go, go!
Go down there, quick!

78
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:46,125
- Mummy?
- Don't be afraid, I am here.

79
00:07:50,875 --> 00:07:52,708
They're coming.

80
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:12,917
Halt!

81
00:08:44,542 --> 00:08:49,333
Attention, attention.
To all the residents of this street.

82
00:08:50,792 --> 00:08:54,458
All fire arms have to be
turned in immediately.

83
00:08:55,958 --> 00:08:58,875
This is the last warning.

84
00:08:59,292 --> 00:09:01,958
Attention, attention.

85
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:05,208
This is the last warning.

86
00:10:00,042 --> 00:10:01,625
Attack!

87
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:17,208
Upstairs!

88
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:20,750
All the way upstairs!

89
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:36,000
Go away! Not now!

90
00:10:36,208 --> 00:10:37,167
Attention!

91
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:09,875
I... I have...

92
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:31,500
Careful!

93
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:34,042
Comrade Colonel.

94
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:37,500
The troops have almost
reached Potsdam station.

95
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,125
But the order was to go towards
the government district!

96
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:47,833
Understood,
Comrade Colonel.

97
00:11:52,417 --> 00:11:53,958
We'll stay here.

98
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,042
Major! I thought we were
going to the Reichstag.

99
00:11:56,667 --> 00:11:58,250
No Reichstag? But why not,
we are so close.

100
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:01,458
Screw it,
we are not staying here!

101
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,792
That's an order!

102
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:08,000
Retreat!
Secure our flank!

103
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:12,208
Understood?

104
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:18,458
Soldiers?
Officers?

105
00:12:20,042 --> 00:12:21,625
Weapons?

106
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:25,292
I said: Soldiers?
Officers?

107
00:12:26,458 --> 00:12:30,000
They will see soon enough.

108
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:34,250
Anybody got weapons?
Hand them over.

109
00:12:34,708 --> 00:12:36,792
Get out!
One person at a time.

110
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:51,625
Get out, all of you!
Move it!

111
00:12:52,417 --> 00:12:54,958
- Russian filth!
- Up!

112
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:02,083
What... do you want?

113
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:09,875
Russian?

114
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:12,792
Yes.

115
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,792
Russian!

116
00:13:20,875 --> 00:13:22,167
Come.

117
00:13:22,667 --> 00:13:23,625
Come.

118
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:26,167
Eat.

119
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:31,542
War kaput.

120
00:13:32,542 --> 00:13:33,500
Woman.

121
00:13:33,917 --> 00:13:36,333
Come! Eat.

122
00:13:38,042 --> 00:13:40,042
War kaput, woman.

123
00:13:40,125 --> 00:13:41,167
Come on.

124
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:44,500
No fear.

125
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:46,708
No fear.

126
00:13:56,292 --> 00:13:59,375
We will not die here.

127
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:23,167
Bravo, come, come.

128
00:14:24,042 --> 00:14:25,583
Don't be afraid.

129
00:14:26,875 --> 00:14:27,833
Come.

130
00:14:28,875 --> 00:14:30,625
Don't shiver!

131
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:32,958
Good! Come.

132
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,500
Hey, cuties!
Come over here.

133
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:43,750
You be nice and you'll
get something to eat.

134
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,417
Potatoes. Very good.

135
00:15:35,917 --> 00:15:37,917
May I?

136
00:16:09,958 --> 00:16:12,500
Does anybody know
how this thing works?

137
00:16:12,917 --> 00:16:14,500
You, Ukrainian,
do you know it?

138
00:16:14,542 --> 00:16:18,208
There they are,
our Russian liberators.

139
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:20,292
Full of joy.

140
00:16:20,458 --> 00:16:25,208
It seems they can hardly believe
that they've made it this far.

141
00:16:25,375 --> 00:16:27,917
I know them,
their sandals and villages.

142
00:16:27,917 --> 00:16:31,458
Their rapidly constructed new
buildings they are so proud of.

143
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,000
Stop!

144
00:16:33,167 --> 00:16:36,000
They are without any constraints.

145
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,125
Don't move,
asshole!

146
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:39,375
Leave her.

147
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:43,042
Get lost.

148
00:16:56,125 --> 00:16:58,500
Urine.
Why don't you use urine?

149
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:02,708
That's enough!

150
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:03,958
No, seriously...

151
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:06,292
Your urine is much too old.

152
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:11,042
Back in Leningrad, I put my general
back on his feet with urine...

153
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,375
You storyteller!

154
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:16,458
It's true.

155
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,583
What are they doing?

156
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:28,417
Please!

157
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:30,333
Please!

158
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:34,125
Have you husband?

159
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:37,458
A husband and two children.

160
00:17:42,708 --> 00:17:45,542
Come anyway.

161
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:51,000
Quick, quick!
Let me through! Let me through!

162
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:57,667
No, no, you pigs.

163
00:17:57,833 --> 00:18:00,667
You pigs! No!

164
00:18:01,917 --> 00:18:06,000
- You don't belong here.
- I didn't do anything wrong.

165
00:18:06,083 --> 00:18:07,125
Stop.

166
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:10,833
You filthy pigs, leave me alone!
Come on, don't be so prude.

167
00:18:10,958 --> 00:18:15,000
Most fellow countrymen adeptly
saved their own hides.

168
00:18:15,125 --> 00:18:18,750
The girl from Silesia was easy prey.

169
00:18:19,208 --> 00:18:20,250
Leave!

170
00:18:21,708 --> 00:18:23,708
Mrs. Hitler.

171
00:18:27,792 --> 00:18:29,375
You slut! Where to?

172
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,083
To the Fuhrer?

173
00:18:34,417 --> 00:18:38,333
Here. Quick.
Penthouse to the right. Quick! Go!

174
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:44,000
Take this and go! Go!

175
00:18:44,292 --> 00:18:45,333
Come.

176
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:53,833
You speak Russian.
You can't abandon me like that.

177
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:02,250
Soldier!

178
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:11,500
Why are you taking a woman...

179
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:14,583
who doesn't want you?

180
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,708
Willing women are unclean.

181
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,750
Open the door! Open it!

182
00:19:41,875 --> 00:19:44,917
Open the door,
you bastards! Open it!

183
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,375
Not here.

184
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:54,333
- Where?
- Almost there.

185
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:04,250
Stop! Stay where you are!

186
00:21:08,458 --> 00:21:09,750
Hey you.

187
00:21:09,917 --> 00:21:11,292
Shoo shoo!

188
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:18,417
Commander...

189
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,500
I am looking for
the commanding officer.

190
00:21:20,708 --> 00:21:22,333
What's up?

191
00:21:23,792 --> 00:21:25,458
Are you in charge here?

192
00:21:25,875 --> 00:21:28,708
I... we need help.

193
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:37,375
Are you in charge here?

194
00:21:38,792 --> 00:21:41,958
There are many in charge here.
Everybody is in charge.

195
00:21:43,542 --> 00:21:44,667
Which one do you want?

196
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:49,667
Major, sir...

197
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:54,000
We need your help...

198
00:21:56,167 --> 00:21:59,167
Our men are all healthy and clean.

199
00:22:24,542 --> 00:22:26,542
Mrs. Hitler.

200
00:22:27,375 --> 00:22:30,292
Our country is finished.

201
00:22:31,375 --> 00:22:35,083
Gerd, do you remember your first words?

202
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:40,750
"Give me 30 minutes and you will
never want to leave me again."

203
00:22:42,667 --> 00:22:44,708
God almighty.

204
00:23:47,083 --> 00:23:51,083
- That is the back corridor.
- The widow offered me a place to stay.

205
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:56,500
She took me by the hand and just led me
inside her undestroyed apartment.

206
00:23:58,625 --> 00:24:05,583
- I gratefully accepted the offer.
- You can stay here for a while.

207
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:12,042
Moving places was easy: a blouse,
a few books and notebooks.

208
00:24:12,542 --> 00:24:16,583
- You are welcome to stay.
- Thank you, I'll take your offer.

209
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:32,167
Take good care of yourself.

210
00:24:37,208 --> 00:24:41,333
In spite of everything, it would have
been good to have a closer look around.

211
00:24:41,917 --> 00:24:47,250
But then, we never know everything,
so that's how the story continued.

212
00:25:02,750 --> 00:25:05,667
I guess it has been
really nice here once.

213
00:25:07,792 --> 00:25:11,292
How did you find me here?

214
00:25:12,833 --> 00:25:15,875
I searched every cellar.

215
00:25:32,208 --> 00:25:34,208
How often?

216
00:25:40,958 --> 00:25:42,042
Often.

217
00:25:48,167 --> 00:25:49,542
The shores are clad in green,

218
00:25:49,625 --> 00:25:52,167
the trees are breathing
freely and deeply

219
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,542
We bravely stride on and on,

220
00:25:54,917 --> 00:25:57,000
towards the final assault
in this war!

221
00:25:58,917 --> 00:26:00,875
Our path was long to reach
this day in May.

222
00:26:01,042 --> 00:26:03,500
It has cost us much
strength and courage.

223
00:26:03,708 --> 00:26:06,042
But now we are free again!

224
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:09,208
We proudly take our positions.

225
00:26:10,417 --> 00:26:11,542
Greetings, May.

226
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:18,250
Our soldiers and a few American weapons,
and those would be history.

227
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:18,625
Yeah.

228
00:26:31,542 --> 00:26:34,583
Yesterday at the water pump,
it was my turn,

229
00:26:34,583 --> 00:26:35,875
a guy approaches me,

230
00:26:37,167 --> 00:26:41,917
two Iron Crosses and one German
Cross in Gold on his chest,

231
00:26:42,083 --> 00:26:46,167
and he gallantly takes the buckets
out of my hands. And I say:

232
00:26:46,333 --> 00:26:52,542
"How do I deserve this honor?"
and he says "We can't give up now"

233
00:26:53,208 --> 00:26:56,917
"because if the Russian
even remotely does to us

234
00:26:57,083 --> 00:27:01,083
"what we did to them
during the last four years,

235
00:27:01,875 --> 00:27:05,542
"in the near future there won't
be any living Germans left."

236
00:27:08,917 --> 00:27:11,958
"In the near future"?
Nobody talks like that.

237
00:27:18,958 --> 00:27:24,792
Hey you Slavs!
We're in Berlin! We made it!

238
00:27:37,917 --> 00:27:42,750
How do you say: Excuse me,
do you have a dictionary?

239
00:27:43,792 --> 00:27:48,000
I guess he doesn't need a
dictionary for what he wants.

240
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:04,250
Lenchen!

241
00:28:16,125 --> 00:28:18,125
Come with us!

242
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:20,792
Come where?

243
00:28:22,125 --> 00:28:23,125
Lenchen!

244
00:28:23,292 --> 00:28:27,208
During the next few days,
our house was raided day and night.

245
00:28:27,375 --> 00:28:29,167
Lenchen!

246
00:28:29,708 --> 00:28:34,042
One woman hanged herself,
another one was shot to death.

247
00:28:34,208 --> 00:28:36,417
None of us was spared.

248
00:28:36,583 --> 00:28:39,625
Every emotion is dead.

249
00:28:40,083 --> 00:28:41,167
Hey, you from Berlin!

250
00:28:41,292 --> 00:28:43,667
Over here! Upstairs.
What kept you so long?

251
00:28:43,792 --> 00:28:46,917
Berlin is ours.
Germany is ours.

252
00:28:47,333 --> 00:28:48,792
Forever!

253
00:28:49,333 --> 00:28:50,875
Lenchen.

254
00:28:53,333 --> 00:28:56,375
- What have you got there?
- A map.

255
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:05,917
Move it! Faster.

256
00:29:06,125 --> 00:29:07,792
You go left,
I go right.

257
00:29:16,833 --> 00:29:19,208
Where are you going?
Come to us.

258
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,875
Come.

259
00:29:27,875 --> 00:29:32,417
Wake up, damned of the earth,
who are living in hunger and misery.

260
00:29:32,583 --> 00:29:36,875
Justice is about to burst through
like glowing magma in a volcano.

261
00:29:55,083 --> 00:29:58,167
You just go away, away!

262
00:30:08,625 --> 00:30:10,083
I!

263
00:30:24,625 --> 00:30:26,250
I...

264
00:30:26,333 --> 00:30:28,042
