01:32:11,958 --> 01:32:12,167
No.

803
01:32:13,208 --> 01:32:15,708
First she will be interrogated.

804
01:32:16,583 --> 01:32:18,583
Do you understand?

805
01:32:18,833 --> 01:32:20,125
What are you doing, brother?

806
01:32:21,167 --> 01:32:24,042
This woman has sheltered
an armed soldier.

807
01:32:24,083 --> 01:32:25,583
The punishment for that is death.

808
01:32:25,750 --> 01:32:26,958
Go, now!

809
01:32:34,042 --> 01:32:36,917
I'll have to report this.

810
01:32:37,625 --> 01:32:40,667
Burn them alive!

811
01:32:48,333 --> 01:32:53,417
How could you risk our lives like that?
Now we are sold down the river.

812
01:33:21,833 --> 01:33:23,583
Traitor!

813
01:33:38,083 --> 01:33:43,583
I own whole Berlin! Hotel Adlon,
Wedding, Kaiserdamm!

814
01:33:44,083 --> 01:33:46,917
Red flags everywhere.

815
01:33:47,125 --> 01:33:50,542
Red flags.
Pretty flags, good quality.

816
01:33:53,208 --> 01:33:55,333
What is it?

817
01:33:59,208 --> 01:34:00,375
Quarrel?

818
01:34:12,333 --> 01:34:13,542
What are you looking at?

819
01:34:14,000 --> 01:34:15,917
Get out of my sight.

820
01:34:20,417 --> 01:34:21,500
Hey, what's up?

821
01:34:22,500 --> 01:34:23,625
To victory, Commander.

822
01:34:24,333 --> 01:34:26,083
To Stalin and our victory.

823
01:34:26,667 --> 01:34:28,042
Wait.
You should stay with your people.

824
01:34:28,333 --> 01:34:30,333
The war is over.

825
01:34:32,208 --> 01:34:34,500
Here! I get it.

826
01:34:35,292 --> 01:34:36,750
Look...

827
01:34:36,958 --> 01:34:38,917
Lyoba, Marina, Olga.

828
01:34:41,542 --> 01:34:42,750
They love me,

829
01:34:43,625 --> 01:34:45,083
all of them.

830
01:34:46,417 --> 01:34:48,458
Everything all right?

831
01:34:51,000 --> 01:34:53,042
Do you want something to eat?

832
01:35:05,292 --> 01:35:11,708
Here. What's better? You tell me.
His dick or my bicycle?

833
01:35:13,875 --> 01:35:14,958
And you, get out of here...

834
01:35:15,083 --> 01:35:16,875
before I shoot your nuts off!

835
01:35:19,000 --> 01:35:20,083
You, listen!

836
01:35:20,542 --> 01:35:21,792
We celebrate.

837
01:35:22,000 --> 01:35:24,208
Everybody come, whole house.

838
01:35:24,208 --> 01:35:25,000
Order!

839
01:35:27,167 --> 01:35:31,542
Your Hitler is not human.
He is a stinking pile of turd.

840
01:35:33,792 --> 01:35:34,917
Not human.

841
01:35:35,542 --> 01:35:36,792
Turd!

842
01:35:38,250 --> 01:35:40,750
Lenchen, Lenchen!
Trouble upstairs!

843
01:35:40,750 --> 01:35:42,917
Everyone, come now.

844
01:35:44,042 --> 01:35:45,083
Order!

845
01:35:47,125 --> 01:35:48,417
Fill the glasses.

846
01:35:49,000 --> 01:35:50,292
What are you standing there?

847
01:35:50,375 --> 01:35:52,042
We've got guests.

848
01:36:03,333 --> 01:36:05,375
Why fear?

849
01:36:17,125 --> 01:36:20,417
Look down there.
What do you see?

850
01:36:22,917 --> 01:36:24,333
Soldiers.

851
01:36:25,958 --> 01:36:29,667
Russians! Beasts.
Or animals, like you call us.

852
01:36:30,833 --> 01:36:32,875
And you're right.

853
01:36:33,000 --> 01:36:39,333
None of us is hesitating a single
second if we can shoot a German.

854
01:36:40,500 --> 01:36:43,875
Your blood is on our uniforms.

855
01:36:44,250 --> 01:36:47,458
Is good as it is.
None of them wanted war!

856
01:36:48,833 --> 01:36:52,792
Most of them didn't even
know what that is, Germany.

857
01:36:56,500 --> 01:36:59,542
Now come with me.

858
01:37:04,083 --> 01:37:06,167
What is happening here?

859
01:37:06,167 --> 01:37:08,417
Careful, that's mahogany.

860
01:37:09,292 --> 01:37:11,833
Let me go!

861
01:37:16,208 --> 01:37:19,792
- You dance. Dance!
- How dare you?

862
01:37:19,917 --> 01:37:23,333
This is my living room
and not a dance hall.

863
01:37:23,333 --> 01:37:24,375
You understand?

864
01:37:24,542 --> 01:37:27,625
- That is fantastic.
- No dance hall!

865
01:37:27,917 --> 01:37:31,625
Drink Schnapps, Vodka.
Schnapps good.

866
01:37:35,125 --> 01:37:36,250
You.

867
01:37:44,375 --> 01:37:48,375
Sing? Now he wants me to sing.
I won't sing now.

868
01:37:50,125 --> 01:37:53,208
- What does he want?
- Well, have a guess.

869
01:37:53,792 --> 01:37:54,792
No.

870
01:37:55,000 --> 01:37:56,500
What does that mean, "no"?

871
01:37:58,917 --> 01:38:01,958
That is Europe!
That is Europe!

872
01:38:02,625 --> 01:38:04,042
Drink, drink.

873
01:38:06,042 --> 01:38:07,125
Why not?

874
01:38:07,333 --> 01:38:09,292
I'm looking at you.

875
01:38:09,333 --> 01:38:11,500
And you?
Nothing.

876
01:38:17,917 --> 01:38:19,500
Well, maybe next time.

877
01:38:20,458 --> 01:38:21,667
To you.

878
01:38:37,333 --> 01:38:39,417
I Anatol.

879
01:38:41,167 --> 01:38:44,125
- I know.
- Brbel.

880
01:38:45,083 --> 01:38:49,958
My heart calls Brbel.

881
01:38:51,292 --> 01:38:54,458
Brbel, Brbel, Brbel.

882
01:39:06,833 --> 01:39:09,042
I play the fiddle.

883
01:39:09,167 --> 01:39:11,292
Violin. Violin?

884
01:39:11,958 --> 01:39:13,625
You play the piano?

885
01:39:13,708 --> 01:39:16,042
In an orchestra,
but not any more.

886
01:39:16,042 --> 01:39:17,333
The violin is lost.

887
01:39:17,917 --> 01:39:20,875
That's good.
I'd like to play the piano, too.

888
01:39:27,292 --> 01:39:30,250
Why don't you go upstairs?

889
01:39:30,958 --> 01:39:35,625
- Should I?
- Yes, have some fun.

890
01:39:38,750 --> 01:39:41,708
We all need that.

891
01:39:42,375 --> 01:39:45,042
Do you come with me?

892
01:39:45,208 --> 01:39:46,500
Later.

893
01:39:48,042 --> 01:39:50,125
- Sure?
- Yes.

894
01:39:56,542 --> 01:39:59,500
It's good that you are here.

895
01:40:18,875 --> 01:40:21,458
I want to embrace you

896
01:40:21,583 --> 01:40:24,250
my whole life.

897
01:40:27,083 --> 01:40:30,042
I am here, you're in Moscow.

898
01:40:32,208 --> 01:40:35,167
Nobody has arms that long.

899
01:40:35,875 --> 01:40:37,917
Try it.

900
01:40:44,958 --> 01:40:50,208
The Major asked me to call him Andrej.
"Why not?", I said.

901
01:40:50,333 --> 01:40:54,458
"The war is over."
He looked at me for a long while.

902
01:40:55,750 --> 01:40:59,875
"Every newborn child
cries for war," he said.

903
01:41:00,583 --> 01:41:05,333
Nothing and nobody, no man,
no nation, will stop this vicious circle.

904
01:41:06,333 --> 01:41:08,375
Only death.

905
01:41:16,625 --> 01:41:19,708
Not so fast,
I am getting sick.

906
01:41:25,708 --> 01:41:27,500
Gee.

907
01:41:30,458 --> 01:41:31,958
Attention.

908
01:41:34,250 --> 01:41:36,542
And now for everybody...

909
01:41:36,917 --> 01:41:40,292
"I in love with you."

910
01:41:42,583 --> 01:41:43,875
Brbel.

911
01:42:15,167 --> 01:42:16,750
Dance.

912
01:42:22,125 --> 01:42:24,458
Come on, let's go.

913
01:42:32,042 --> 01:42:36,083
We are not a people any more,
we're only "the population".

914
01:42:36,208 --> 01:42:40,125
I am talking about individuals
that form within a democracy.

915
01:42:40,250 --> 01:42:44,375
The ones who get the economy going.
Economic upswing.

916
01:43:11,250 --> 01:43:14,208
Dance, dance, you come.

917
01:43:18,917 --> 01:43:21,875
I think we should look at
the greater picture here.

918
01:43:21,875 --> 01:43:24,500
The countries of Europe
will burst their borders.

919
01:43:24,625 --> 01:43:28,708
They will grow into larger areas.
The victorious super powers will,

920
01:43:28,833 --> 01:43:31,917
just like Napoleon did,
re-order the political world map.

921
01:43:32,292 --> 01:43:36,708
So we will become a Soviet republic
with planned economy, huh?

922
01:43:49,667 --> 01:43:50,750
Thanks.

923
01:43:53,417 --> 01:43:57,458
Well, Mr. Hoch, everything all right?
We need to think practical now.

924
01:43:57,583 --> 01:44:01,583
Let's start the every day life again,
and we will soon get into the groove.

925
01:44:05,250 --> 01:44:06,250
Slow down.

926
01:44:29,333 --> 01:44:30,542
Drink.

927
01:44:42,625 --> 01:44:45,167
The Soviet Union is just at
the beginning of its evolution.

928
01:44:46,417 --> 01:44:49,083
The future will prove that.

929
01:44:52,125 --> 01:44:54,625
You love your country.

930
01:44:55,417 --> 01:44:57,792
Just as I love mine.

931
01:45:06,375 --> 01:45:09,333
My mother once said that one day,

932
01:45:09,833 --> 01:45:13,833
I would marry a man
who played the piano.

933
01:45:22,458 --> 01:45:26,000
Everybody has been wondering
what this day would be like.

934
01:45:28,208 --> 01:45:30,500
I haven't.

935
01:45:31,542 --> 01:45:34,000
Never.

936
01:45:42,208 --> 01:45:45,750
I didn't want to experience it.

937
01:45:51,500 --> 01:45:54,667
Why not?

938
01:46:09,917 --> 01:46:14,625
If you don't do it, Andrej,
I will tell you something.

939
01:46:20,333 --> 01:46:24,625
War is changing the words.

940
01:46:29,250 --> 01:46:34,583
"Love" is not what it used to be.

941
01:46:41,333 --> 01:46:43,375
And yet,

942
01:46:47,083 --> 01:46:49,750
in spite of that,

943
01:46:50,958 --> 01:46:55,500
I want that my husband finds the
same wife that he left behind

944
01:46:55,542 --> 01:46:58,083
when he returns.

945
01:47:03,583 --> 01:47:05,625
Please stay.

946
01:47:27,250 --> 01:47:31,375
Us women,
we are branded for life.

947
01:47:32,833 --> 01:47:37,250
But for here and now,
right in this moment,

948
01:47:38,667 --> 01:47:41,750
I feel fantastic.

949
01:47:50,917 --> 01:47:54,000
I'll go and get us some tea.
Ilse still has some left.

950
01:48:30,958 --> 01:48:34,708
Morning, Lenchen!
Anybody up?

951
01:48:41,083 --> 01:48:44,167
- Where is your Wanja?
- Working.

952
01:48:45,417 --> 01:48:47,458
And mummy?

953
01:48:52,958 --> 01:48:54,042
Ilse?

954
01:48:56,000 --> 01:48:57,000
Ilse?

955
01:49:00,333 --> 01:49:01,958
Ilse?

956
01:49:19,333 --> 01:49:20,792
Ilse.

957
01:49:22,167 --> 01:49:24,833
Ilse, get away from him.

958
01:49:40,333 --> 01:49:43,333
Gerd, do you remember?
It was on a Tuesday.

959
01:49:43,458 --> 01:49:46,000
We went to see Felix.

960
01:49:46,125 --> 01:49:49,208
You could smell the tree resin.

961
01:49:49,833 --> 01:49:53,958
We came across a cloud of butterflies.

962
01:49:56,083 --> 01:49:59,167
And you knew all their names.

963
01:49:59,625 --> 01:50:06,167
Pea blues, Brimstones, Fire birds,
Swallowtails and many more.

964
01:50:11,125 --> 01:50:13,917
One was taking a sunbath
right there on the path,

965
01:50:13,917 --> 01:50:16,167
it was velvety brown and
yellow with a blue hem.

966
01:50:16,792 --> 01:50:19,875
You called it a Mourning Cloak.

967
01:50:48,625 --> 01:50:52,333
So many things I've
been given in my life.

968
01:50:52,333 --> 01:50:53,375
In abundance.

969
01:50:53,500 --> 01:50:56,583
The Major had lost everything.

970
01:50:56,875 --> 01:50:59,875
Damn Russian idealist.

971
01:51:00,000 --> 01:51:04,042
He takes it all like he
wants the world to be.

972
01:51:04,167 --> 01:51:07,125
Soviet apostle.

973
01:51:09,833 --> 01:51:11,417
I like him though.

974
01:51:11,500 --> 01:51:15,375
The less he wants from me,
the more I like him.

975
01:51:17,042 --> 01:51:18,167
Very much.

976
01:51:26,667 --> 01:51:27,792
Andrej.

977
01:51:30,292 --> 01:51:31,333
Andrej.

978
01:52:02,417 --> 01:52:05,375
Andrej isn't here any more.

979
01:52:07,167 --> 01:52:08,750
Relocated.

980
01:52:15,542 --> 01:52:16,667
To where?

981
01:52:21,667 --> 01:52:23,125
Unknown.

982
01:52:25,583 --> 01:52:26,917
Good-bye.

983
01:53:30,042 --> 01:53:33,125
"The birds so quiet,
the bells are silent."

984
01:53:33,500 --> 01:53:36,625
(from "18 Little Songs of the
Bitter Homeland" by Yiannis Ritsos)

985
01:53:37,083 --> 01:53:39,750
Isn't that how it goes?

986
01:53:57,667 --> 01:53:59,000
Please, sit down.

987
01:54:25,500 --> 01:54:27,625
The studio,

988
01:54:29,542 --> 01:54:31,583
is that gone?

989
01:54:44,917 --> 01:54:48,000
- I don't live here alone.
- I know.

990
01:54:52,000 --> 01:54:54,583
Ukrainians like that.

991
01:55:47,667 --> 01:55:50,625
Here, that's for you.

992
01:56:57,542 --> 01:57:00,208
You are shameless.

993
01:57:00,542 --> 01:57:03,208
Don't you see that?

994
01:57:06,792 --> 01:57:10,500
It is disgusting
just to look at you.

995
01:58:11,167 --> 01:58:12,458
Atten-shun!

996
01:58:47,125 --> 01:58:50,292
- I'd like to thank you.
- For what?

997
01:58:53,750 --> 01:58:56,833
That I had the chance
to get to know you.

998
01:59:06,333 --> 01:59:09,292
Take care of yourself.

999
01:59:25,667 --> 01:59:28,667
How are we supposed to live?

1000
02:00:03,500 --> 02:00:05,583
Eyes front!

1001
02:00:19,958 --> 02:00:23,125
"Relocation," that's what they call it.

1002
02:00:24,958 --> 02:00:27,917
With full honors and merits.

1003
02:00:28,042 --> 02:00:31,667
To Siberia, who knows?

1004
02:00:53,833 --> 02:00:55,250
Gerd.

1005
02:00:56,333 --> 02:00:59,292
My beloved Gerd.

1006
02:01:00,125 --> 02:01:03,042
What shall we do?

1007
02:01:03,167 --> 02:01:05,792
Turn back the wheel of time?

1008
02:01:05,917 --> 02:01:09,000
Back to your very first words?

1009
02:01:10,375 --> 02:01:13,333
"30 minutes", you said.

1010
02:01:17,500 --> 02:01:23,375
"Give me 30 minutes, and you will
never want to leave me again."

1011
02:04:01,208 --> 02:04:02,208
What?

1012
02:04:16,958 --> 02:04:18,083
What?

1013
02:04:25,083 --> 02:04:27,750
No answer.

1014
02:04:28,500 --> 02:04:31,583
Two days later he was gone.

1015
02:04:32,042 --> 02:04:35,042
I don't know if he will come back.

1016
02:04:35,167 --> 02:04:38,750
I am surprised that I am
not suffering more.

1017
02:04:38,750 --> 02:04:39,792
Maybe I am just too busy.

1018
02:04:40,708 --> 02:04:44,417
I need to find a piece of flint stone,

1019
02:04:44,542 --> 02:04:47,667
I need to mop up the
floor of the apartment

1020
02:04:47,667 --> 02:04:50,625
and I am desperately
looking for some flowers.

1021
02:04:50,750 --> 02:04:53,708
Yesterday I found some lilac.

1022
02:04:54,958 --> 02:04:57,917
I wonder if Gerd still thinks about me.

1023
02:04:58,125 --> 02:05:00,167
Who knows?

1024
02:05:00,333 --> 02:05:02,750
Maybe our hearts have
a say in this, too,

1025
02:05:02,958 --> 02:05:06,417
and we'll see each other again,
some day.

1026
02:05:09,542 --> 02:05:13,958
When the diary "A woman in Berlin"
was first released in Germany in 1959,

1027
02:05:14,042 --> 02:05:15,583
it was a huge scandal.

1028
02:05:15,667 --> 02:05:20,000
Many people said that it was a disgrace
and an insult to the German women.

1029
02:05:20,292 --> 02:05:24,042
The author was so shocked by
the rejection and the contempt
that her book received.

1030
02:05:24,542 --> 02:05:28,208
She prohibited any further
releases for as long as she lived.

1031
02:05:28,625 --> 02:05:31,417
And even beyond her death,
here real name was never to be revealed.

